of
use.
"Martin,
before
we
separate,
assure
me
seriously,
and
on
your
word
of
honour,
that
Mr.
Moore
is
better."
"How
very
much
you
think
of
that
Moore!"
"No
but
many
of
his
friends
may
ask
me,
and
I
wish
to
be
able
to
give
an
authentic
answer."
"You
may
tell
them
he
is
well
enough,
only
idle.
You
may
tell
them
that
he
takes
mutton
chops
for
dinner,
and
the
best
of
arrowroot
for
supper.
I
intercepted
a
basin
myself
one
night
on
its
