upstairs,
and
ate
half
of
it."
"And
who
waits
on
him,
Martin?
who
nurses
him?"
"Nurses
him?
The
great
baby!
Why,
a
woman
as
round
and
big
as
our
largest
water
butt
a
rough,
hard
favoured
old
girl.
I
make
no
doubt
she
leads
him
a
rich
life.
Nobody
else
is
let
near
him.
He
is
chiefly
in
the
dark.
It
is
my
belief
she
knocks
him
about
terribly
in
that
chamber.
I
listen
at
the
wall
sometimes
when
I
am
in
bed,
and
I
think
I
hear
her
thumping
him.
You
should
see
her
fist.
She
could
hold
half
a
dozen
hands
like
yours
in
her
one
palm.
